==Details==
{{Quest details page|Garden of Tranquillity}}

==Walkthrough==
===Starting out===
'''Note:''' If you are only looking for the Ring of Charos(a), only doing this section will suffice. You will need 1 free inventory slot and (optional) 2 compost of any kind. 
{{Checklist|
*Talk to [[Ellamaria]] at the garden east of [[Varrock Palace]]. {{Chat option|1I would be happy to help someone who is so in touch with the people.}}
**Optionally you could place your compost early in the 2 empty plant pots north to save inventory spaces after speaking to Ellamaria.
*Talk to Ellamaria again to obtain the trolley. {{Chat option|1How am I supposed to move statues all the way here?}}
*Talk to the [[Wise Old Man]] in [[Draynor Village]] north of the bank with the [[ring of charos]]. {{Chat option|1Queen Ellamaria has sent me to seek your guidance.}}
*Quiz answers:
**Show them a range of colours so that they can come to a compromise.
**Take his generous gift even though you have no need for it.
**It's absolutely, unquestionably the most interesting thing I've ever done!
**Put on the silly helmet and jump into the cannon.
**You of course Pkmaster0036, no one could ever challenge your greatness!
**Ask me nicely and I might consider it.
**No, especially not that wise old man, who doesn't look at all suspicious.
}}

===Gathering seeds===
{{Checklist|
*See to the survival of your crops as you see fit.
*Always have on you: a rake, seed dibber, spade, secateurs, watering can, gardening trowel, and ring of charos(a). You may use the tool leprechauns by the patches.
*Equip the ring of charos(a).
}}
* '''Note:''' You '''must''' speak to the farmers before planting the crops. '''No crops may be planted in advance.'''
===Elstan north-west of Draynor===
''Item required: a marigold seed.''
{{Checklist|
*Talk to [[Elstan]]. {{Chat option|1Do you have any delphinium seeds to spare?|2(Charm) That is why I have come to an expert for advice.|3(Charm) Not just AN expert, Elstan - they say you are THE expert.|2(Charm) Oh no, I love listening to gardening stories...|2(Charm) Millions? Ah, just what I wanted to hear...|1Okay, I'll grow you some marigolds.}}
*Grow marigolds in the patch ([[Ultracompost]] highly recommended).
*Once grown, give them to Elstan for the delphinium seeds {{Chat option|1 Okay, I've grown those marigolds like you asked.}} (You can continue the quest before finishing this step.)
}}

===Lyra north-west of Port Phasmatys===
''Items required: 3-6 onion seeds.''
{{Checklist|
*Talk to [[Lyra]]. {{Chat option|1Do you have any orchid seeds to spare?|2(Charm) If you tell me your problems, I may be able to help you.|2(Charm) Yes, I was wondering about that.|2(Charm) Times must be very hard for you.|2(Charm) Whatever you've done, I'm sure you had just cause.|2(Charm) And what is the nature of this fee that you pay?|2(Charm) If not yours, then whose blood are you offering?|2(Charm) How can you deal with so much guilt?|1That's a deal - I'll grow a patch of onions for you.}}
*Grow onions (both patches reduce chance of failure).
*Once grown, talk to Lyra for the orchid seeds. {{Chat option|1Okay, I've grown those onions like you asked.}} (You can continue the quest before finishing this step.)
}}
===Kragen north of Ardougne===
''Items required: 3-6 cabbage seeds.''
{{Checklist|
*Talk to [[Kragen]]. {{Chat option|1Do you have any snowdrop seeds to spare?|2(Charm) You seem to be a little irritable, my friend.|2(Charm) I don't like to see a fellow human being so upset.|2(Charm) So what ails you, my friend?|2(Charm) Well, is there anything I can do for you?|2(Charm) So what can I do for you?|1That's a deal - I'll let you know when your cabbages are ready.}}
*Grow cabbages (both patches reduce chance of failure).
*Once grown, talk to Kragen for the snowdrop seeds. {{Chat option|1Okay, I've grown those cabbages like you asked.}} (You can continue the quest before finishing this step.)
}}
===Dantaera in Catherby===
''Item required: secateurs, gardening trowel, a filled plant pot (can be bought from the nearby store), a filled watering can.''
{{Checklist|
*Talk to [[Dantaera]] at the Catherby farming patch. {{Chat option|1Do you know how I could grow a White Tree?|2(Charm) I think that there is something you are not telling me.|2(Charm) A secret is a dreadful burden to have to keep to yourself.|2(Charm) Unless you allow me to do this she will die anyway.}}
*Travel to [[Ice Mountain]], next to Edgeville Monastery.
*Use secateurs on the [[White tree|White Tree]] located on the northern part of the Ice Mountain.
*Put the [[White tree shoot]] in your plant pot and '''water it'''.
}}
===Brother Althric at the Edgeville monastery===
''Item required: a fishing rod and ring of charos(a).''
{{Checklist|
*Talk to [[Brother Althric]] at the Edgeville monastery. {{Chat option|2(Charm) These are the most beautiful rosebushes I've ever seen.}}
*Run over to Edgeville and throw the ring of charos(a) down the well.
*Go back to the monastery and pick 4 seeds from the red, pink, and white roses.
*Retrieve your ring with a fishing rod (this could take a few tries) or return to Fenkenstrain's Castle if you destroyed it.
**(Optional) Use the sink in the house west of the well to refill your watering can.}}

===Bernald behind the Burthorpe pub===
''Items required: a rune/pure essence, a hammer, 2 plant cures, a pestle and mortar and ring of charos(a).''
{{Checklist|
*Talk to [[Bernald]] (in the fenced in area beside the bar), while wearing ring of charos(a). {{Chat option|2(Charm) But it is the only way that these vines will be cured.|1I accept the deal.}}
*Use 1 plant cure on the vines.
*Talk to Bernald again.
*Talk to [[Alain]] (with the Ring of charos UN-equipped) by the Taverley tree patch. {{Chat option|1I need to ask you about strong plant cures.|1Are you sure there's nothing you can suggest? }}
*Crush rune/pure essence with a hammer then grind the shards with a pestle and mortar.
*Add this to the other plant cure and use it on the vines.
*Talk to Bernald to get the vine seeds.
}}

===Returning to planted crops===
{{Checklist|
*Return to Elstan south of Falador. Pick the marigolds and give them to Elstan. {{Chat option|1I have those marigolds for you.}}. 
*Return to Lyra north-west of Port Phasmatys {{Chat option|1Okay, I've grown those onions like you asked.}}. You do not need to harvest the onions.
*Return to Kragen north of Ardougne {{Chat option|1Okay, I've grown those cabbages like you asked.}}. You do not need to harvest the cabbages.
*You may come back to these steps if the crops are not yet grown. Depending on what growth tick you planted on, your plants should be 80-90% grown by the time you reach this step (see "growth timing" under Mechanics on the [[Farming]] page).
}}
===Varrock Castle===
''Items required: 2 buckets of compost (super, ultra work as well. Bottomless compost will not work), a seed dibber, a rake, a spade and ring of charos(a), all acquired seeds.''{{Checklist|
*Fill the 2 plantpots with compost. *Note that using the Bottomless Compost Bucket does not work here!
*Plant yellow orchids in the east pot, and pink orchids in the west pot.
*Plant all acquired seeds in the palace garden according to their labeled plots.
**Plant the White tree in the centre patch.
** The White tree takes a long time to grow. You can reduce the time you must wait if you plant the tree just before a [[growth cycle]].
*Talk to [[Ellamaria]] for the trolley if you haven't already.}}

===Lumbridge Castle===
{{Checklist|
*Use the trolley on the statue of a king (southern statue just outside Lumbridge castle gates).
**If at any point you logout or lose your trolley, speak to [[Ellamaria]] to get another.
*Push (or '''big push''') the trolley east over the bridge then place it on the northern plinth in the garden.}}
===Falador square===
{{Checklist|
*Use the trolley on the statue.
*Watch the cutscene.
*Push the trolley north through the gate then place it on the southern plinth in the garden.
}}
===Finishing up===
{{Checklist|
*Wait until every plot is fully grown (takes 10-15 minutes).
*Once fully grown, talk to [[Ellamaria]].
*Talk to [[King Roald]]. {{Chat option|1Ask King Roald to follow me.|2(Charm) Of course, your majesty - please forgive me.|2(Charm) The Queen asked me to bring you.}}
**Make sure you have the ring of charos (a) equipped when talking to King Roald or he will not follow you.
*Watch the cutscene. 
**{{colour|Red|Warning:}} Interrupting the queen after the cutscene will cause it to play all over again!
*(Optional) Pick some fruit from the white tree to complete a Varrock medium task (will take a few minutes to produce fruit).
}}
'''Quest complete!'''

